PRIORITY critical
MEMORY SYSTEM RULES (DEPRECATED)
TSVI now at ../../shared/skills/agents/01-memory.md. DNET file — edit the shared version. LS: 2026-05-02 
SS PROTOCOL
Every agent MUST follow this order on SS: 
Read INDEX.md for the active brand/project — always first Read known-issues.md — required before touching any code Read stack.md only if the task requires technical detail Read decisions.md only if the task touches past decisions Read changelog.md only to log changes at session end 
NLAF at once. INDEX.md covers 90% of sessions. 
ACTIVE SESSION CONTROL
The .active-session file in memory root contains one word — the active brand name. Never read memory files for a brand other than the active session brand. 
SESSION END PROTOCOL
AECT: 
Append one line to the relevant MEMORY.md: [YYYY-MM-DD] — [task] — [outcome] Update INDEX.md Last 3 Changes section If any error happened twice: add to known-issues.md 
WHAT GOES IN MEMORY VS CONTEXT
Put in memory Keep in context DM CT details Known issues Code being written Stack details User instructions Change history Errors in this session 
TOKEN BUDGET
INDEX.md: ~400 tokens (always fine) stack.md: ~600 tokens (load only if needed) decisions.md: ~800 tokens (load only if needed) changelog.md: ~1000 tokens (load only to write) NEVER exceed 3000 tokens of memory context per session 